  "texts": [
    "Further research comparing different ML tools would be beneficial in gaining a more comprehensive understanding of the performance of these learning algorithms in educational research synthesis.",
    "Our current study provides a foundational step in this area, and we recommend it as an essential focus for future research.",
    "Overall, the results suggest that learning algorithms can reduce screening time in a wide range of educational and educational psychology systematic reviews and point to differences between learning algorithms that should be considered when using an ML-based abstract screening tool.",
    "As the learning algorithms (e.g., RF + SBERT) investigated in this study are also used in other ML-based screening tools, the performance insights gained in this study are likely to apply to other tools employing these shared learning algorithms.",
    "The use of active learning algorithms on text data from the education field was not previously studied."
